        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&REPLY_ID=33827&TOPIC_ID=4530&FORUM_ID=1&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=General+Discussions&Topic_Title=What+can+you+kill+with+Shadowbound+Deflux+49pet%3F&M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>


        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">You can kill some stuff...  Let me give you an example.  With Vexing Mordania, Deflux, Shadowbound, tanking a bit myself, darkness, splurt, and 56th focused pet I can take on drolvarg/skeletal guardians, decaying prisoners, skeletal lookouts, and probably even some skeletal watchers(131 hitting type) if I softed them up a bit with DoT & rooting first.  The thing is, your pet isn't going to survive by itself with just shadowbound with the damage mobs are dealing at higher levels and your only hope truly is to get yourself some ac gear and go at it toe to toe like you used to at lower levels.  Deflux is a fast enough spell that as long as you manage your hp wisely, you shouldn't die.  Of course, a few interrupts and a resist on root and it's all over for you, so becareful when soloing like this.</P><P>I still prefer DoT & Rooting in almost all circumstances, especially if you understand how pathing and fear works at certain places.  It really sucks, IMO, that a caster only has 8 spell slots.  I can imagine doing alot more if only I could mem 2 extra spells with the previous setup: Screaming Terror and Invoke Fear.  With those spells, a necro maybe able to do some level 48-49 mobs with pets, but again anything that summons usually spells death to the necro, period.  The necro pet truly isn't that state of the art and I'd recommend using root & doting in anything that does not involve very MR mobs or outdoor fear kiting.</P><P></P><P><BR>Etadanik the Redeemed<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
